<div class="xar-mod-head">
  <span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Courses Administration</xar:mlstring></span>
</div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">

  <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <p>
    <em><xar:mlstring>Courses is the documented Xaraya Courses Module.</xar:mlstring></em>
    <xar:mlstring>It is currently responsible for accomplishing these main tasks:</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Manages the course offerings to students.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Users can enroll into courses.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Produces overviews of courses, participants and the planning.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Sends out registration emails.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Allow teachers to be attached to a course, so they can manage their own course.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
  <h3><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <p>
            <xar:mlstring>To set up the course offerings you will need to understand the way courses are setup.</xar:mlstring>
            <xar:mlstring>Courses are single entities that are present in the system. The information regarding a course is rather fixed. Courses are offered to users in Xaraya, this means they are planned.</xar:mlstring>
            <xar:mlstring>Once the course is planned, you can attach more information to the planned course like a start date, maximum number of participants, location etc.</xar:mlstring>
  </p>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring></h3>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Upcoming courses. This is a block which shows the courses in the near future</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>We plan to offer another Admin Block with short term information</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
  <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring></h3>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>usermenu -- Allows interface with the "My Account Page"</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>search -- Allows interface with Search Module</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
  <p>
    <xar:mlstring>
      In these cases, the Courses module provides the hook functionality.
      To activate the hooks go to </xar:mlstring>
    <a href="&xar-modurl-modules-admin-hooks;&amp;hook=courses"><xar:mlstring>Modules - Configure Hooks - Courses Module</xar:mlstring></a>.
    <xar:mlstring> From there click on the checkbox in either Roles or
      the Search module to activate the respective hooks.
    </xar:mlstring>
  </p>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Dynamic Data Properties</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Courselisting -- Provides a dropdown of courses</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>This listing can be used in other modules or in your own template</xar:mlstring></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>
    <xar:mlstring>Further Information</xar:mlstring>
  </h3>
  <p>
    <xar:mlstring>Further information on the Courses module can be found at</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Courses Extension page at</xar:mlstring> <a title="#xarML('Courses Module - Xaraya Extension 179')#" href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/release/179.html">Xaraya Extension and Releases</a>.
      <xar:mlstring> Click on Version History tab at the bottom to get the latest release information.</xar:mlstring>
    </li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Related tutorials and documentation on Courses found at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/keywords/courses/" title="#xarML('Related documentation on Courses')#"><xar:mlstring>Xaraya Documentation.</xar:mlstring></a>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="xar-sub">
    <strong>&nbsp;<xar:mlstring>Courses Module - Overview</xar:mlstring></strong><br />&nbsp;<xar:mlstring>Version</xar:mlstring> 1.0.1&nbsp; 2006-01-22
  </p>
</div>

